  ],
  "text": "Audit of Chromium's renderer process sandbox implementation found the following key files:\n\n1. **BaselinePolicy** (seccomp-BPF baseline for Linux): `sandbox/linux/seccomp-bpf-helpers/baseline_policy.cc` — implements the `BaselinePolicy` class (declared in `baseline_policy.h`), which is the foundational seccomp-BPF policy applied to all sandboxed Linux processes. It defines which syscalls are allowed, denied, or conditionally handled.\n\n2. **PolicyBase** (Windows sandbox policy): `sandbox/win/src/sandbox_policy_base.cc` — implements the `PolicyBase` class (declared in `sandbox_policy_base.h`), which is the concrete implementation of the `TargetPolicy` interface for Windows sandboxing. It manages sandbox configuration, process restrictions, and IPC dispatching for sandboxed target processes.\n\n3. **RendererProcessPolicy** (Linux BPF renderer policy): `sandbox/policy/linux/bpf_renderer_policy_linux.cc` — implements `RendererProcessPolicy::EvaluateSyscall()`, the BPF policy specific to renderer process sandboxing on Linux. This class extends `BPFBasePolicy` and defines the syscall allowlist tailored for renderer processes (and worker processes).\n\n4. **SandboxType utilities and enum**: `sandbox/policy/sandbox_type.h` declares utility functions (`IsUnsandboxedSandboxType`, `SetCommandLineFlagsForSandboxType`, `SandboxTypeFromCommandLine`) that map between command-line flags and sandbox types. The actual `Sandbox` enum (with values like `kRenderer`, `kGpu`, `kNetwork`, `kNoSandbox`, etc.) is defined in `sandbox/policy/mojom/sandbox.mojom` as `sandbox::mojom::Sandbox`."
}

